<subSubSection id="C36A8DB4FF8FFFAAFF64FE1CFF070A06" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF8FFFAAFF64FE1CFF070A06" blockId="42.[142,758,416,1051]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFF64FE1CFF200FA8" box="[142,243,416,437]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Remarks</emphasis>
: The family 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFE7EFE1CFDEE0FAB" authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1980" box="[404,573,416,438]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bythograeidae</taxonomicName>
, first described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFF58FE03FEB90FC8" author="Williams AB" box="[178,362,447,469]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="443 - 472" refId="ref80814" refString="Williams AB. 1980. A new crab family from the vicinity of submarine thermal vents on the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (2): 443 - 472." type="journal article" year="1980">Williams (1980)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFDDCFE03FF350FEF" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermydron">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFDDCFE03FF350FEF" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Bythograea thermydron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from vents in the eastern Pacific, remains the only family of crabs truly endemic to deep-sea hydrothermal vents. To date, the family is represented by five genera: 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFEF0FD85FF140C70" authority="Guinot, Hurtado &amp; Vrijenhoek, 2002" authorityName="Guinot, Hurtado &amp; Vrijenhoek" authorityYear="2002" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Allograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFEF0FD85FE5B0C53" box="[282,392,569,590]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Allograea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE7AFD85FF140C70" author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA &amp; Vrijenhoek R" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="1143 - 1152" refId="ref66774" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA, Vrijenhoek R. 2002. New genus and species of brachyuran crab from the southern East Pacific Rise (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 325 (11): 1143 - 1152." type="journal article" year="2002">Guinot, Hurtado &amp; Vrijenhoek, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFF03FDE4FD210C70" authority="Hessler &amp; Martin, 1989" authorityName="Hessler &amp; Martin" authorityYear="1989" box="[233,754,600,622]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Austinograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFF03FDE4FE530C70" box="[233,384,600,621]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Austinograea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE77FDE4FD210C70" author="Hessler RR &amp; Martin JW" box="[413,754,600,622]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="645 - 661" refId="ref67925" refString="Hessler RR, Martin JW. 1989. Austinograea williamsi, new genus, new species, a hydrothermal vent crab (Decapoda: Bythograeidae) from the Mariana Back-Arc Basin, western Pacific. Journal of Crustacean Biology 9 (4): 645 - 661." type="journal article" year="1989">Hessler &amp; Martin, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFF64FDCBFE0A0C91" authority="Williams, 1980" authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1980" box="[142,473,631,653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFF64FDCBFEC30C91" box="[142,272,631,652]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Bythograea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFEC8FDCBFE0A0C91" author="Williams AB" box="[290,473,631,653]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="443 - 472" refId="ref80814" refString="Williams AB. 1980. A new crab family from the vicinity of submarine thermal vents on the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (2): 443 - 472." type="journal article" year="1980">Williams, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFE05FDCBFEE10CB7" authority="de Saint Laurent, 1984" authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1984" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Cyanagraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFE05FDCBFDAB0C91" box="[495,632,631,652]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Cyanagraea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFD61FDCBFEE10CB7" author="de Saint Laurent M" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="355 - 360" refId="ref75616" refString="de Saint Laurent M. 1984. Crustaces decapodes d'un site hydrothermal actif de la dorsale du Pacific oriental (13 ° Nord), en provenance de la campagne francaise Biocyatherm. Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris, serie III 299: 355 - 360." type="journal article" year="1984">de Saint Laurent, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF8FFFAAFE9AFD2AFD420CB7" authority="Guinot, 1989" authorityName="Guinot" authorityYear="1989" box="[368,657,661,683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Segonzacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFE9AFD2AFE3C0CB6" box="[368,495,662,683]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">Segonzacia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE13FD29FD420CB7" author="Guinot D" box="[505,657,661,683]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="203 - 231" refId="ref66559" refString="Guinot D. 1989. Description de Segonzacia gen. nov. et remarques sur Segonzacia mesatlantica (Williams): campagne HYDROSNAKE 1988 sur la dorsale medio-Atlantique (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, serie IV 11: 203 - 231." type="journal article" year="1989">Guinot, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. All species are assumed to be predators rather than bacterial feeders or grazers (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE37FD6FFF140D1A" author="Gorodezky LA &amp; Childress JJ" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="123 - 131" refId="ref66408" refString="Gorodezky LA, Childress JJ. 1994. Effects of sulfide exposure history and hemolymph thiosulfate on oxygen consumption rates and regulation in the hydrothermal vent crab Bythograea thermydron. Marine Biology 120 (1): 123 - 131." type="journal article" year="1994">Gorodezky &amp; Childress, 1994</bibRefCitation>
); indeed, they are probably top predators at vent sites (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFEECFCACFE770D38" author="Jollivet D" box="[262,420,784,806]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" refId="ref68588" refString="Jollivet D. 1993. Distribution et evolution de la faune associee aux sources hydrothermales profondes a 13 ° N sur la dorsale du Pacifique Orientale: le cas particuliere des polychetes Alvinellidae. These de Doctorat nouveau regime, Universite de Bretagne Occidentale." type="book" year="1993">Jollivet, 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE59FCACFD9B0D38" author="Voight J" box="[435,584,784,806]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="155 - 166" refId="ref79934" refString="Voight J. 2000. A review of predators and predation at deepsea hydrothermal vents. Cahiers Biologie Marine 41: 155 - 166." type="journal article" year="2000">Voight, 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFDBDFCACFF1B0D58" author="Micheli F &amp; Peterson CH &amp; Mullineaux LS &amp; Fisher CR &amp; Mills SW &amp; Sancho G &amp; Johnson GA &amp; Lenihan HS" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="365 - 382" refId="ref72258" refString="Micheli F, Peterson CH, Mullineaux LS, Fisher CR, Mills SW, Sancho G, Johnson GA, Lenihan HS. 2002. Predation structures communities at deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Ecological Monographs 72 (3): 365 - 382." type="journal article" year="2002">
Micheli 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF8FFFAAFD5DFCADFD3C0D38" box="[695,751,784,806]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">et al.</emphasis>
, 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). The southern extent of the family, as is currently known, appears to be at approximately 
<geoCoordinate id="EE44B8F8FF8FFFAAFF64FCD0FF100D9C" box="[142,195,876,897]" degrees="40" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" precision="55555" value="-40.0">40°S</geoCoordinate>
, as indicated by observations of unnamed bythograeids by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFEBEFC37FD260DBC" author="Stecher J &amp; Turkay M &amp; Borowski C" box="[340,757,907,929]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="271 - 274" refId="ref77304" refString="Stecher J, Turkay M, Borowski C. 2002. Faunal assemblages on the Pacific-Antarctic Ridge near the Foundation Seamount Chain (37 ° 30 ' S, 110 ° 30 ' W). Cahiers de Biologie Marine 43: 271 - 274." type="journal article" year="2002">Stecher, Türkay &amp; Borowski (2002)</bibRefCitation>
from the Foundation Seamount Chain of the Pacific- Antarctic Ridge and by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF8FFFAAFE43FC74FD650DC3" author="Clark MR &amp; O'Shea S" box="[425,694,968,990]" pageId="42" pageNumber="487" pagination="14 - 17" refId="ref63477" refString="Clark MR, O'Shea S. 2001. Hydrothermal vent and seamount fauna from the southern Kermadec Ridge, New Zealand. InterRidge News 10 (2): 14 - 17." type="journal article" year="2001">Clark &amp; O’Shea (2001)</bibRefCitation>
from the Kermadec Ridge off 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF8FFFAAFE4BFC5BFDE80DE0" box="[417,571,999,1021]" name="New Zealand" pageId="42" pageNumber="487">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, slightly further north.
</paragraph>
